#. module: bookstore
#: model_terms:product.template,description:bookstore.product_product_12_product_template
msgid ""
"Most startups are built to fail. But those failures according to "
"entrepreneur Eric Ries are preventable. Startups don t fail because of bad "
"execution or missed deadlines or blown budgets. They fail because they are "
"building something nobody wants. Whether they arise from someone s garage or"
" are created within a mature Fortune 500 organization new ventures by "
"definition are designed to create new products or services under conditions "
"of extreme uncertainly. Their primary mission is to find out what customers "
"ultimately will buy. One of the central premises of The Lean Startup "
"movement is what Ries calls validated learning about the customer. It is a "
"way of getting continuous feedback from customers so that the company can "
"shift directions or alter its plans inch by inch minute by minute. Rather "
"than creating an elaborate business plan and a product-centric approach Lean"
" Startup prizes testing your vision continuously with your customers and "
"making constant adjustments -- Every so often a business book comes along "
"that changes how we think about innovation and entrepreneurship. Eric Ries s"
" The Lean Startup has the chops to join this exalted company."
msgstr ""
"De fleste startups er dømt til at fejle. Men ifølge iværksætteren Eric Ries "
"er mange af disse fiaskoer faktisk til at undgå. Startups går sjældent under "
"på grund af dårlig eksekvering, forsinkede deadlines eller "
"budgetoverskridelser. De fejler, fordi de udvikler produkter, som ingen "
"reelt efterspørger. Uanset om de opstår i en garage eller etableres inden "
"for rammerne af en Fortune 500-virksomhed, er nye virksomheder pr. "
"definition sat i verden for at skabe nye produkter eller tjenester under "
"ekstrem usikkerhed. Deres vigtigste opgave er derfor at finde ud af, hvad "
"kunderne faktisk vil betale for. En af grundpillerne i Lean Startup-"
"bevægelsen er det, Ries kalder valideret kundelæring: en metode til løbende "
"at indsamle feedback fra kunderne, så virksomheden kontinuerligt kan justere "
"kursen – trin for trin, næsten minut for minut. I stedet for at basere sig "
"på detaljerede forretningsplaner og en ensidigt produktfokuseret tilgang "
"lægger Lean Startup vægt på konstant at afprøve sin vision i dialog med "
"kunderne og tilpasse den undervejs. Med jævne mellemrum udkommer der en "
"økonomibog, som grundlæggende ændrer vores syn på innovation og "
"iværksætteri. Eric Ries’ The Lean Startup har potentiale til at indtage en "
"plads i denne eksklusive kategori."

